    "In addition, interest in this technology has increased due to features such as the absence of a third-party controlling the transactions and the anonymity of the parties [36].",
    "Blockchain structureEach block in a blockchain consists of two parts: the header and the body.",
    "As seen in Figure 2, the header of a block includes a timestamp, a Merkle root, a summary of the previous block, and a ''nonce'' value.",
    "The timestamp holds the current time information.",
    "The Merkle root has a binary tree structure and all transactions in the block body are contained in the leaves."
